This paper is about object detection and segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a deep learning architecture for this task, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing a loss function, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of recursive neural networks (RNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques, such as similarity measures and structured loss, which suggests that it could also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
